column5: Hi all,  Got out a few days ago for some local walleye action, bite was tough, morning mist spectacular and the chill in the air a constant reminder that I better get my snowblower tire fixed soon.
There's a crack in your windshield!  Seriously love you'r commute, what'd I see, like three cars until you hit town?
And I knew the people in the first 2vehicles I passed....gotta love small towns....gene pool could do with a refresh though.....lol.
Nice tour of your roads and trek out to your fishing hole.
I was concerned  half way through the video and you hadn't even started fishing  but it happened and I love watching them on the fishfinder chasing the bait
I believe you exceeded the posted speed on a few occasions and failed to come to a complete stop at 2 stop signs. I have forwarded the video to the local authorities. Great camera work Simon.
Fun camers work with the finder. Was this Lac Suel?
Great video Simon. The drive looked familiar
Awesome report Simon Felt like was right there along. Great job on the video.
Youre hooked on the gopro now!  Some awesome footage of course
